|   BITWISE NOT
|
|   EXAMPLES: 
|
| y = 5;  x = 3;
| 
| Y in Binary = 000101
| X in Binary = 000011
|   NOT = OPPOSITE
| ~Y = 111010
| ~X = 111100
|
| y = 10; x = 16;
|  
|        
|  ~101011101 = 010100010  
|  ~101001010 = 010110101
|  ~111001010 = 000110101
|  ~110001101 = 001110010
|  ~000001010 = 111110101
|  ~111010111 = 000101000
|
|For example.
|~0 = the highest possible number. All bits are 1.
|~0 = 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 11
|
|_____________________________________




